@node ShAsk_1
@title "Command specification"
@{b}Command specification@{ub}

                                    @{b}ShAsk@{ub}

@{i}Format:@{ui}           ShAsk <prompt> [TIMEOUT=<n>] [DEFAULT=<s>]

@{i}Template:@{ui}         PROMPT/A,TIMEOUT/K/N,DEFAULT/K

@{i}Purpose:@{ui}          To prompt the user with a requester to acquire
                  a yes or no response.

@{i}Path:@{ui}             ShAsk/

@{i}Specification:@{ui}

ShAsk is used similar to the built-in CLI command Ask. For more information
about the operation of the command, please refer to the "Using The System
Software" manual, p. 8-11.

A major difference to the original Ask command is, that ShAsk prompts
the user with a requester, rather than just printing the text string.
A timeout feature was also added. A user control over it is provided
by the use of two new command line arguments.

The actual timeout value is determined by "TIMEOUT=<n>" in which <n> is
the number of seconds to wait for user to make his choice of yes or no.
If the user fails to click either button in that time, the default is
returned. The default value returned when timeout occurs can be set
using "DEFAULT=<s>" in which <s> is either "YES" or "NO".

Both of these new arguments are optional and if they are absent, default
values will be used. By default timeout feature is disabled, so the
requester will not go away without the user making a choice, if TIMEOUT
is not defined. Default return value is Yes. "TIMEOUT=0" would disable
the timeout feature, but this is actually useless, because it is off by
default. Also specifying "DEFAULT=YES" is useless, because it's the
default value also. The keywords and the default specification are case
insensitive.

@{i}Example:@{ui}          ShAsk "Run TechnoBBS?" TIMEOUT=10 DEFAULT=NO

This would ask the user whether he or she wants to run his or hers
TechnoBBS software. If he or she won't answer in ten seconds the
default value comes to life and TechnoBBS will not be run.

@{i}See also:@{ui}         Ask,Else,EndIf,If
@endnode
@node ShAsk_2
@title "Registration"
@{b}Registration@{ub}

If you like ShAsk and use it repeatedly, please send a contribution of
2,5 FIM to the author. Naturally contributions of a greater amount are
also welcome. This way you'll help us develope even more and even better
software for the Amiga. Future releases from us include a serial
controller for TechnoBBS, a WWF manipulator, an RDB scanner and much more.
@endnode
